place.name: STODY
place.gazetteerText: STODY, a parish in Erpingham district, Norfolk; 3 miles SW of Holt, and 8 NE of Ryburgh r. station. Post town, Thetford. Acres, 1,277. Real property, £1,453. Pop., 160. Houses, 31. The property is sub-divided. The living is a rectory, united with Hunworth, in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £342. Patron, the Marquis of Lothian. The church is cruciform, and has a round tower. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
